Text.Value: A dangerous upbringing. It made you strong.
Even if I personally faced down the Army of the Absolute, and drove it from the city single-handedly, I would not be welcomed as a saviour.

EditorData.NodeContext: thinking of her background as a villain - she doesn't trust the surface world to ever see her as otherwise. contemptuous of this rather than sad

Text.Value: Menzoberranzen is not fertile ground for such messages. I killed them, and hanged their bodies in my garden.

EditorData.NodeContext: with a cruel smile - reflecting on her first encounter with the cult of the Absolute

Text.Value: They'd be right to.
I was born there - I'm surprised we never crossed paths.
Little wonder you find it hard to make friends if your own mother tried to kill you.
He invited me to the head of his table, as his guest of honour. I was wary, of course. If I had been in his position, the food would have been poisoned.

EditorData.NodeContext: reflecting on her first meeting with Ketheric

Text.Value: Let her speak.
As it turned out, to my shame, I was defeated without even drawing my weapon.

EditorData.NodeContext: mild regret, and some anger. doesn't like admitting her failures

Text.Value: They were fools to encroach on Lolth's territory.
We had barely begun to eat when she spoke for the first time. I only caught one word - my name.

EditorData.NodeContext: regret and anxiety

Text.Value: We were both born of trauma, both raised by parents who protected us with one hand and tormented us with the other.
You waged war against Moonrise?
Ketheric expected us - expected me - and I fell for his flattery.

EditorData.NodeContext: reflecting on her first meeting with Ketheric

Text.Value: Do you know who sent them?
From the cult and the illithids? Of course. And then I suspect I want exactly what Gortash wants.

EditorData.NodeContext: talknig about being a saviour to the city, and then moving on to conquering it afterwards

Text.Value: Ketheric proposed an alliance between Moonrise and Menzoberranzan. I admit, I was captivated by him.

EditorData.NodeContext: reflecting on her first meeting with Ketheric

Text.Value: I do not want to be tolerated, I want to be feared. Don't you?

EditorData.NodeContext: curious

Text.Value: A joke. I am no more Orin than you are.
How is that possible?
You know me well.
Though I am proud, I prefer exile to death.

EditorData.NodeContext: With pride and a little sadness, talking of her exile from her home city, Menzoberranzan

Text.Value: And nobody would remember me.
If we come out of this alive - together - surely that's enough?

Synopsis: Default Dialogue - the conversation you can have with Minthara at any thime when she's a member of your party. You can ask her about herself, or events that you've experienced together during your adventures. Her responses to you may differ based on some of the choices you make after she joins. Provided you don't betray her for another, she will continue to stand by you, revelling in the violence that follows.
